# Shell Environment Setup

Every shell session must prepend Python and append Git, Databricks CLI, and fnm to the PATH. Run this **once per session** before any dev command:

```powershell
$env:PATH = "C:\Users\NH136948\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python312;C:\Users\NH136948\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python312\Scripts;" + $env:PATH + ";C:\Users\NH136948\AppData\Local\Programs\Git\cmd;C:\Users\NH136948\AppData\Local\Microsoft\WinGet\Packages\Databricks.DatabricksCLI_Microsoft.Winget.Source_8wekyb3d8bbwe;C:\Users\NH136948\AppData\Local\Microsoft\WinGet\Packages\Schniz.fnm_Microsoft.Winget.Source_8wekyb3d8bbwe"
fnm env --use-on-cd --shell power-shell | Invoke-Expression
```

Python must be prepended (not appended) to override the Windows Store `python.exe` alias.

## Verify with
```powershell
python --version && node --version && npm --version && git --version && databricks --version
```
